The first universities of Muslims also originated from the Islamic Mosque Asinpur Akhri. Apart from this, Islamic architecture has also developed mainly from mosques.
The word masjid literally means place of prostration or 'prostration'. This word is often used in the languages   of Muslims including Urdu. This is an Arabic caste word. The word 'mosque' is used for it in English and European languages, although many Muslims now use mosque (Masjid) in English and other European languages   because in their view it is derived from the Spanish word Moska. Is derived from. But in the opinion of some people this is not right. Near Ahle Islam, there is the mosque, the building where prayers are offered. If prayers are offered in a mosque even on Friday, then it is called Jama Masjid. The word Masjid has also appeared in the Quran, as in the context of Masjid-Haram, this word has been used in countless verses.
